@startuml
title Interactive Session — State Machine (with History)

[*] --> MenuDisplay : session starts\n(Calculator + OperationRegistry\n+ OperationHistory created)

MenuDisplay --> OperationSelection : show numbered menu

OperationSelection --> OperationSelection : invalid index\n(re-prompt, retry_count++)
OperationSelection --> Terminating : MAX_ATTEMPTS exceeded
OperationSelection --> OperandInput : valid index selected

OperandInput --> OperandInput : invalid operand\n(ValueError — re-prompt, retry_count++)
OperandInput --> Terminating : MAX_ATTEMPTS exceeded
OperandInput --> Computing : valid operand(s) provided

Computing --> Recording : registry.call() success
Computing --> ContinuePrompt : exception\n(no history entry)

Recording --> ContinuePrompt : history.record() called\n(entry appended to _entries)

ContinuePrompt --> ContinuePrompt : unrecognised input\n(re-prompt)
ContinuePrompt --> MenuDisplay : yes / y
ContinuePrompt --> Terminating : no / n

Terminating --> Persisting : history.write_to_file()\n(errors caught, logged to stderr)
Persisting --> [*] : session returns

note bottom of Persisting
  write_to_file() is called at ALL 5 exit points:
  1. User selects "no" at continue prompt
  2. MAX_ATTEMPTS exceeded during op selection
  3. MAX_ATTEMPTS exceeded during operand 1 input
  4. MAX_ATTEMPTS exceeded during operand 2 input
  5. Any unhandled early-exit path
end note

@enduml
